The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Frankfurt, Aug. 27: Volkswagen plans to invest up to 400 million euros ($511.1 million) to set up a plant in India, Der Spiegel magazine has reported. The firms supervisory board will make a decision on the move at a meeting next month, though it is not expected to be contested, the magazine said. As is known, the carmaker is examining entry into the Indian market. We are not commenting on further details, a Volkswagen spokesman has said.

 New Delhi, Aug. 27: Stung by the comptroller and auditor generals (CAG) criticism of PSU selloff, former disinvestment minister Arun Shourie said the CAG had taken a very narrow perspective but thanked finance minister P. Chidambaram for a fair response on the issue.

 New Delhi, Aug. 27: The commerce ministry has strongly contested the finance ministrys claim that SEZs would lead to a revenue loss of Rs 92,000 crore, and has said the government stands to gain Rs 44,000 crore from them.

 Calcutta, Aug. 27: The Emami group will set up a bio-diesel plant at Haldia over the next 18 months at a cost of Rs 150 crore. The plant would be the first large bio-diesel project undertaken in the organised sector in Bengal.

 New Delhi, Aug. 27: Assocham has said the commodity futures market size is expected to more than double by 2010 to Rs 12,00,000 crore.




